The party's contesting two by-elections in George on Wednesday following the death of DA and ANC councillors. CAPE TOWN The African National Congress (ANC) in the Western Cape has roped in the party's deputy president, Cyril Ramaphosa, to campaign ahead of by-elections. The party's contesting two by-elections in George on Wednesday following the death of Democratic Alliance and ANC councillors.Ramaphosa, along with deputy ministers Zou Kota-Fredericks and Mcebisi Skwatsha, met voters in Uniondale and Thembalethu on Monday.Door-to-door in Uniondale, George, with #ANCDPRamaphosa ahead of, 01 February 2017, #ByElections #UnityInAction pic.twitter.com/HKPX6OAdrrThe party s provincial secretary Faiez Jacobs says they are hoping the deputy president's presence is a good omen. His presence here will add an impetus for our election campaign. He does inspire us and gives us hope that we can do a big election push. We are calling out on all our members and supporters to come out and vote in both Thembalethu and Uniondale. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)